metadata.label: Description
value: Collection of training manuals, brochures, maps, and postcards collected by a member of the Renshū Kantai on a trip to the United States and Central America in 1936. The earliest-published item in the collection is a Rand-McNally map published in 1923.  Inserted into a commercially produced "scrap book" (B-size) of unidentified manufacture. Some items inserted in pockets, others pasted in.

metadata.label: Note
value: Materials in Japanese, English, and Spanish.
